    "body": "This is to report a bug in the Spack on-line docs, specifically in the \r\n[page discussing RPackage build system](https://spack.readthedocs.io/en/latest/build_systems/rpackage.html)\r\nIn the section \"Passing arguments to the configuration\", it lists the method\r\n<configure_args(self, spec, prefix)>, however the actual code (lib/spack/spack/build_systems/r.py) declares this method as only taking <self> as an argument (and uses it in that fashion).\r\n\r\nThis looks to be a simple error in the docs",
